    body: 'A **Hard** success requires the roll to come in at or under **half** your skill, rounding down. Persuade 70 means a Hard success on **01–35**.\n\nThe Keeper calls for Hard difficulty when the task is meaningfully harder than routine — talking past a guard who has already been warned, spotting a detail deliberately concealed. Rolling over half but under your full value on a **Hard** roll is a **failure**, not a partial win.\n\nHard also appears as a threshold in resolution: some opposed contests and some weapon effects care specifically about whether you cleared the half mark.',
