    body: 'A d100 result of **01** is a **critical success**. It always succeeds, regardless of the difficulty level called for and regardless of how low the skill is — a 3% skill still criticals on 01.\n\nA critical is a licence for the Keeper to give you more than you asked for: the perfect angle, the extra clue, the shot that ends it. In combat a critical does the same damage an **Extreme** success would.\n\nNote what it is NOT. There is no "crit range", no doubling of dice, no confirmation roll. It is exactly one result on one die pair.',
