    short: 'A roll of 100 always fumbles; so does 96–99 when the skill being rolled is below 50.',
    body: 'A **fumble** is a failure that actively makes things worse. Two cases:\n\n· A result of **100** is always a fumble, no matter how good the skill is.\n· A result of **96–99** is a fumble **only if the skill or characteristic being rolled is below 50**.\n\nThat second clause is the elegant bit — the less competent you are, the wider your fumble band. A Firearms of 20 fumbles on 96–100; a Firearms of 75 fumbles only on 100.\n\nThe Keeper decides the consequence in the fiction: the gun jams, the rope parts, the lie lands catastrophically. A fumbled roll **cannot be pushed** — the failure is already final and messy.\n\n**Luck** cannot be spent to climb out of a fumble either.',
