    short: 'An extra TENS die; keep whichever tens result is better (lower). Not a numeric bonus.',
    body: 'A **bonus die** does not add anything. You roll **one extra tens die** and keep whichever tens result gives you the **better (lower)** final number, with the same single units die.\n\nExample: units die 4, tens dice 6 and 2. Your options are **64** and **24** — with a bonus die you take **24**.\n\nTwo bonus dice means three tens dice, still keeping the best. Bonus dice come from aiming, from a helpful ally, from good circumstances, and from certain abilities. Bonus and **penalty** dice **cancel one for one** before you roll; if any remain, roll that many extra tens dice.\n\nRemember the special case: a tens die of **0** with a units die of **0** reads as **100**, not 00.',
