    short: 'An extra TENS die; you are forced to keep the worse (higher) tens result.',
    body: 'The mirror of a bonus die. Roll **one extra tens die** and keep the **worse (higher)** result.\n\nUnits die 4, tens dice 6 and 2 gives you **64** and **24** — with a penalty die you are stuck with **64**.\n\nPenalty dice model bad conditions: firing at a fast-moving target, working in the dark, acting while badly hurt. **Bonus and penalty dice cancel each other one for one** — three bonus and two penalty leaves you rolling with one bonus die.\n\nThis is deliberately not a −20 modifier. Because it warps the tens die only, a penalty die hurts a low skill far less in absolute terms than a flat subtraction would, and it can never push you below a 1-in-10 chance of the units die saving you.',
