    kind: 'mechanic',
    short: 'Both sides roll against their own skill; the higher LEVEL of success wins, ties go to the higher skill.',
    body: 'When two people directly contest — arm-wrestling, a chase of wits, hiding versus searching — **both** roll against their **own** value.\n\nResolve it by **level of success**, not by margin: Critical beats Extreme beats Hard beats Regular beats failure. Whoever achieved the higher level wins.\n\n· If both achieve the **same level**, the one with the **higher skill value** wins.\n· If those are also equal, roll again.\n· If both **fail**, nothing changes — the status quo holds.\n\nNote what is absent: you never subtract one roll from the other, and there is no "beat their number". Two Regular successes are a tie broken by whose skill is bigger, even if one player rolled 03 and the other rolled 60.\n\nCombat is a chain of opposed rolls: the attacker rolls their weapon skill and the defender chooses to **Fight Back** or **Dodge**. In combat, **ties go to the attacker**.',
