    short: 'The eight core numbers plus Luck, all rated as PERCENTAGES from 0–99, not 3–18 scores.',
    body: 'Investigators have eight characteristics — **STR, CON, SIZ, DEX, APP, INT, POW, EDU** — plus **Luck**. Every one of them is a **percentage**, in the same units as a skill. There is **no modifier table**: the characteristic *is* the target number you roll under, and its **half** and **fifth** values give you Hard and Extreme.\n\nRolling them up:\n\n· **STR, CON, DEX, APP, POW** — **3d6 × 5** (15–90)\n· **SIZ, INT, EDU** — **(2d6 + 6) × 5** (40–90)\n· **Luck** — **3d6 × 5**\n\nOr point-buy: distribute **460 points** across the eight characteristics, **maximum 80** in any one at creation.\n\nDerived values come straight off these: **Hit Points = (CON + SIZ) ÷ 10**, **Sanity = POW**, **Damage Bonus and Build** from STR + SIZ, and **Move** from comparing STR and DEX to SIZ.\n\nAging adjusts them — investigators over 40 take deductions to physical characteristics and gains to EDU, which is why the "seasoned professor" is smart, rich in skills, and easy to kill.',
