    body: '**Sanity (SAN)** starts equal to your **POW** and is tracked separately from it forever after. It is the resource the game is actually about.\n\nYour **maximum Sanity is 99 − your Cthulhu Mythos skill**. Every point of Mythos knowledge you gain permanently lowers the ceiling you can ever recover to. Learn enough about the truth and there is no sane version of you left to return to.\n\nSanity is spent involuntarily via **Sanity checks**, and thresholds fire off it:\n\n· Lose **5 or more** from a single check → possible **Temporary Insanity**\n· Lose **one fifth of your current Sanity** within a single day → **Indefinite Insanity**\n· Reach **Sanity 0** → **permanent insanity**; the investigator is retired to the Keeper\n\nIt comes back in trickles: scenario awards for resolving the horror, and **Psychoanalysis** between sessions. Sanity lost to a direct Mythos encounter is largely never coming back.',
